The paper focuses on the optimization of machine-type communication (mMTC) in 5G networks, which is a subfield of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed protocol involves a non-cooperative game, which falls under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses effective capacity and access class barring, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and system theory (cs.SY), respectively. Finally, the paper deals with traffic types, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
